order.name: RO
order.label: Regular
order.description: A regular order is an order placed during the market hours or the pre-market hours.

types.name: MARKET
types.label: Market
types.description: A market order allows you to buy or sell a stock at the best available price. If you're placing a buy market order, you want to buy a specified quantity of stock from the exchange at any price available.

types.name: LIMIT
types.label: Limit
types.description: A limit order allows you to buy or sell a stock at the price you have set or a better price.

order.name: BO
order.label: Bracket
order.description: Bracket order (BO) is a type of order where you can enter a new position (intraday only) along with a target/exit and a stop-loss order.

types.name: LIMIT
types.label: Limit
types.description: A limit order allows you to buy or sell a stock at the price you have set or a better price.

order.name: CO
order.label: Cover
order.description: A Cover Order is an order which is placed along with a compulsory Stop Loss Order

types.label: Market
types.description: A market order allows you to buy or sell a stock at the best available price. If you're placing a buy market order, you want to buy a specified quantity of stock from the exchange at any price available.

types.name: LIMIT
types.label: Limit
types.description: A limit order allows you to buy or sell a stock at the price you have set or a better price.

order.name: AMO
order.label: After Market
order.description: This facility is available for people who can't actively track the markets from 9:15 AM to 3:30 PM.

products.name: CNC
products.label: No, execute as a long term order
products.description:
You hold the shares in your demat
for a duration of two days or more.

products.name: MIS
products.label: Yes, execute as an intraday order
products.description: A buy order must be sold on the same day and vice-versa before markets close.
